==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marcid
<hw>Mar"cid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>marcidus</ets>, fr. <ets>marcere</ets> to wither, pine.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pining; lean; withered.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by emaciation, as a fever.</def>
<rj><au>Harvey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marcidity</ent>⟦br⟧
